Those willing to take up the job would report to the said schools and start their profession. There were those that never bothered to teach and they had the choice to go for other careers. Those were rather good times for graduates.
Those times are gone and these days, there is a glut of qualified teachers and recruitment has been localised. The commission advertises the posts to be filled in each county as per the needs and thousands upon thousands apply for them.



